title: Three partes of Salomon his Song of Songs, expounded The first part printed before: but now re-printed and enlarged. The second and third partes neuer printed before. All which parts are here expounded and applied for the readers good. By Henoch Clapham.
author: Clapham, Henoch.
publisher: By Valentine Sims for Edmund Mutton dwelling in Pater-noster-Row at the signe of the Huntes-man,
notes: Parts 2 and 3 each have separate dated title page, pagination and register are continuous.
T1 is cancel with duplicate setting; T1r begins with "is" and last line ends either "ther-" or "there". Original T1 begins: "maister".
Reproduction of the original in the Union Theological Seminary (New York, N.Y.). Library.
